Retail Pension Fund Increases Pensions by 1.3%

As of January 1, 2025, the Retail Pension Fund will increase pensions by 1.3%. Read more.

A joining of forces

Long ago, employees and employers decided to work together and wisely invest the money that is deposited each month for retirement.

The result? A staggering wealth that grows and flourishes. This gives employees an extra income to enjoy life when they no longer have to work, in addition to the government pension.

Retiring soon? Here’s what you need to do.

What feels like 'finally!' to one person, is 'already!?' to another. But one thing is certain: when you pass 60, your retirement age is in sight: 67 years. Check here what you need to do to be able to enjoy it later.

We invest for you

Together with your employer, you build up a reserve for later every month. Because saving alone does not yield enough, the money is invested by us in a responsible way in shares, loans from governments and companies, real estate and mortgages.

The largest sector in the Netherlands

From fashion and living to perfumery and drinks: the diversity in retail is great. For the employees in all these sectors, Pensioenfonds Detailhandel is committed every day. Not only by building a good income for later, but also by making pensions as personal as possible.

Compulsory

There is a legal obligation for the Retail Pension Fund. This has been agreed upon by employers' and employees' organisations. This way, the risks are shared and the costs are limited.

Cookie settings

Cookies are small, simple text files that are stored on your computer, phone or other device when you visit our website. These cookies help the website to look and function properly. We call these functional cookies. In addition, this website uses limited analytical cookies. For example, these cookies help to count how many people have visited a page. We do this counting anonymously.

This website does not use tracking cookies.

In order to properly perform our legal task, we do process your personal data. In our privacy statement you can read how we protect your personal data.
